The paper proposes a deep learning architecture for semantic pixel wise image labelling, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The architecture involves a stack of encoders and decoders, which are commonly used in deep learning for image processing tasks such as image segmentation and object detection. Therefore, it is likely that the paper also falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of soft-max classification layer, which is a common technique in neural networks for classification tasks, indicating a possible overlap with neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper tests the performance of the proposed architecture on outdoor and indoor scenes, which suggests a possible overlap with robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
